{"word":"Φῆστος","slug":"Φῆστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Φῆστος, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> festus ‘festal’, also as term of endearment] Porcius <b>Festus,</b> procurator of Judea in the early 60s, successor to Felix (<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Φῆλιξ\">Φῆλιξ</a></el>) <b><a href='B:510 24:27'>Ac 24:27</a>; <a href='B:510 25:1'>25:1</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ch.\">ch.</a> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:φησίν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:φθάνω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}